<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step08_ExceptionHandling"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 8 - Exception Handling">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step08ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 8: Exception Handling in Async Code"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">EXCEPTIONS: Handling errors in async methods.

Good news: try/catch works with async/await just like normal code!
When an awaited task throws an exception, it "bubbles up" to the catch block.

But there are some important things to know:
- A single await: The exception comes through directly, just catch it normally.
- Task.WhenAll: If MULTIPLE tasks fail, only the FIRST exception is thrown by
  default. You need to inspect the task objects to see all exceptions.
- async void methods: Exceptions CANNOT be caught by the caller! They crash
  the app. (This is why we avoid async void except for event handlers.)
- AggregateException: When using Task.WhenAll, the Task.Exception property
  contains an AggregateException that holds ALL the individual exceptions.</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="1. Single task exception (simple try/catch)"
                    Command="{Binding SingleExceptionCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="2. Multiple task exceptions (Task.WhenAll)"
                    Command="{Binding MultipleExceptionsCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="3. Nested async exception (call chain)"
                    Command="{Binding NestedExceptionCommand}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="280"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
